author: Sports Desk
title: Nasir Jamshed arrested in London alongside bookie over fixing
text:
Share Tweet Email Nasir Jamshed. PHOTO : BCCI 
Pakistan left-handed opener Nasir Jamshed was arrested on Tuesday by Britain’s National Crime Agency (NCA) alongside a bookie named Yousuf, Express News reported. 
Jamshed, who is accused of referring Islamabad duo Sharjeel Khan and Khalid Latif to Yousuf, has been provisionally suspended from all forms of cricket on Monday by the Pakistan Cricket Board. 
According to the representative of the NCA, Jamshed and Yousuf have been released on bail and asked to report to the agency in April. 
Pakistan Super League (PSL) chairman Najam Sethi on Monday tweeted the news about his suspension. PCB has provisionally suspended Nasir Jamshed from all forms of cricket for violating its anti-corruption code @TheRealPCB 
— Najam Sethi (@najamsethi) February 13, 2017 
This is a developing story and will be updated accordingly.
